@startuml
title NEIL Solar AMC - Unified User Interaction Flow (Phase 1)

left to right direction

actor Owner
actor Manager
actor Supervisor
actor Technician
actor CustomerSupervisor as Customer

rectangle "FlutterFlow Owner/Manager Portal" as OwnerPortal
rectangle "FlutterFlow Supervisor/Technician App" as FieldApp
rectangle "Customer Mobile Web" as CustomerWeb

rectangle "FastAPI Backend (Cloud Run)" as API
rectangle "Cloud SQL Postgres" as DB
rectangle "GCS Media Bucket" as GCSMedia
rectangle "GCS Reports Bucket" as GCSReports
rectangle "Twilio WhatsApp Sandbox" as Twilio

Owner --> OwnerPortal : signup/login
OwnerPortal --> API : create organization
API --> DB : persist tenant + owner user
API --> OwnerPortal : verification / next steps

Owner --> OwnerPortal : create users and roles
OwnerPortal --> API : invite manager/supervisor users
API --> DB : users, roles, invitations

Manager --> OwnerPortal : login
Manager --> OwnerPortal : create customers
OwnerPortal --> API : customer CRUD
API --> DB : customers

Manager --> OwnerPortal : create AMC sites
OwnerPortal --> API : site CRUD
API --> DB : sites + site supervisor details

Supervisor --> FieldApp : login
Supervisor --> FieldApp : create/invite technicians
FieldApp --> API : user role = TECH
API --> DB : user_roles, invitations

Supervisor --> FieldApp : assign technician to site
FieldApp --> API : create workorder + assignment
API --> DB : work_orders (SCHEDULED)

Technician --> FieldApp : view assigned workorders
FieldApp --> API : fetch assigned list
API --> DB : query work_orders

Technician --> FieldApp : complete checklist + photos + tech sign
FieldApp --> API : submit checklist response (idempotent)
API --> DB : checklist_responses, signatures(TECH)
API --> GCSMedia : store photo/signature objects
API --> DB : update workorder (SUBMITTED)

API --> GCSReports : generate and store draft PDF
API --> DB : report record (is_final=false)

API --> Twilio : send approval link via WhatsApp
Twilio --> Customer : WhatsApp message with tokenized link
API --> DB : approval_events (SENT, expires_in=72h)

Customer --> CustomerWeb : open approval link
CustomerWeb --> API : validate token
API --> DB : token status OPENED if valid

Customer --> CustomerWeb : sign report (single-use token)
CustomerWeb --> API : submit customer signature PNG
API --> DB : signatures(CUSTOMER_SUPERVISOR)
API --> GCSMedia : store customer signature
API --> GCSReports : regenerate final signed PDF
API --> DB : report is_final=true
API --> DB : workorder CUSTOMER_SIGNED -> CLOSED
API --> DB : approval_events SIGNED (token consumed)

Owner --> OwnerPortal : view reports and customer/site status
OwnerPortal --> API : report and visit queries
API --> DB : fetch reports/workorders
API --> GCSReports : signed URL access for PDF

@enduml

